This is part of a series of ordinal refactors which aim to replace definitions specific to `Ordinal` with more general concepts. See #17033 for more info.

The fact that you're moving deprecated lemmas to a separate section makes this PR incredibly hard to review. Furthermore, there are changes beyond the mere replacement of `Ordinal.IsLimit` by `Order.IsSuccLimit`. They should be their own PR. I could only find, but there might be more, it's hard to tell from the diff.

The fact that you're moving deprecated lemmas to a separate section makes this PR incredibly hard to review. Furthermore, there are changes beyond the mere replacement of `Ordinal.IsLimit` by `Order.IsSuccLimit`. They should be their own PR. I could only find, but there might be more, it's hard to tell from the diff.
This authorship claim feels out of place drowned in a big refactor PR which doesn't even touch the file. You should definitely claim authorship, but in one of your other PRs would be best
I think I meant to do this in `Ordinal.Arithmetic` instead, but that one already has my name!
I'm for this change but just noting that I believe it undoes a change by @kim-em
Please don't do this, it makes it harder to count things.

Can you revert changes like this? They make the diff much harder to read than necessary
```suggestion
theorem isSuccPrelimit_zero : IsSuccPrelimit (0 : Ordinal) := isSuccPrelimit_bot
```
What's this universe generalisation doing here?
What's this new theorem doing here?
I've moved my various tweaks to the `Ordinal.pred` API to #21751.
